``linregress``
--------------
Small wrapper class for using R's linear regression functionality in Python,
via `rpy2 <http://rpy.sourceforge.net/rpy2.html rpy2>`_.

Example usage::

    >>> x = [1, 2, 3, 4]
    >>> y = [1.2, 3, 7, 10]
    >>> m = LinearRegression(x=x, y=y, formula='y~x')
    >>> m.slope
    3.0399999999999996

    >>> m.intercept
    -2.299999999999998

    >>> m.adj_r_squared
    0.97221750212404412

    # t-tests using std err allow testing to different expected values
    >>> m.slope_pval(compare_to=0)
    0.0093041159117684229
